snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a massive AJ fan.


Like his persona, I like him as a person though I've never met him, hes genuine. As a boxer hes probably the best we've had in a long long time.
Now, wrt to Deontay Wilder, Somebody below posted: "Wilders not fought anyone who's capable of knocking him out..."
My response to that, is, its not his (Deontay Wilder's) fault.
He fought Tyson Fury and despite tasting leather most of the fight, he had the punching power to put Fury on his backside not the other way around.That has to count for something. Secondly, lets not disrespect the 40 odd fighters DW's fought. They're pro's as far as I'm concerned - not bums.
Not being KO'd in 40 fights is no fluke. Lets get serious here and cut out the biased b/s. Call it like you see it, if its bad ass its bad ass and Deontay Wilder, is bad ass.
I want to see AJ vs Wilder. Not Wilder v Fury 2 tbh.

snippet.textDisplay:
First of, gotta admit... AJ seems very calm and confident, doesn't he? I do think he needs to watch that Wilder-Ortiz fight; then he'd see that beyond the sound bites and the highly, Wilder was a total disappointment until that KO.

Second, Dominique Breazeale fought AJ when AJ was very inexperienced but he got a worse beating than when he fought Wilder - look at his face after the fight! The man needed facial reconstruction. Breazeale was never a top contender, on that fight with Wilder he was slow and posed no threat to Wilder. And he had not fought for a long time. To be honest, I was rooting for him(because I can't stand Wilder - he's fake, sorry!) - I was seriously disappointed because the guy came in there fighting like he was fight Otto Wallin - Slow, weak.

On the other hand, Ortiz won every single round, even that last round; he got too confident as he was making Wilder miss and got set up. How the hell you go'n every single round? The man's performance was worse than when he fought Fury. At least with Fury he(Wilder) had some rounds; he lost every single round with Ortiz on their rematch? Seriously? Man, get the hell out of here! You're supposed to be a boxer and it's sport at the end of the day ffs! I don't rate With bruh, nope... I don't. Not as a boxer, not as a man! talking about if he dies he dies... speak it, believe it, receive it huh! If he dies he dies? And as for Fury changing his coach last minute is not good news at all.

I suppose until the fights do happen we will keep seeing these discussions. One day somebody will need to stop ducking. And soon, wilder or Fury will see their 0 record erased... unless the fight does not happen.

snippet.textDisplay: So many people on here saying proper dumb shit taking pride and propaganda over facts and statistics. Wilders been avoiding AJ for a while now. Wilder was wanting to fight Ruiz for the remaining belts but as soon as Ruiz loses he didn’t want to contest AJ for the remaining belts and is now being slimy as fuck trying to stay relevant for long enough to cash in some more money before everyone realises Wilder is a massive joke. Yeah, he might have a power right hand but that doesn’t mean anything if he brawls like he does, any top tier boxers could have him fairly easily, Fury showed that in the previous fight just got unlucky with being hit by that right. Not forgetting hes not long came out of a long break so Fury wasn’t exactly at his best. Currently wilders the best pound for pound boxer because of his stats but we all know that them stats are pretty bullshit and have no relevance because he’s fought barely relevant people for most of his record. AJ has achieved way more in his career already and he’s not fought nearly as many fights.
